        id: 3030,
        type: 'text',
        title: 'Like a doll',
        epigraph:
          'The fashion itself is centered around dressing like a doll, and, although its exact origin within Japanese society is debatable, the gothic Visual Kei fashion style exhibited by some bands during the ’80s can be credited in part for the initial rise of the fashion movement. There are certainly hints of nostalgia with Lolita, with adults wearing this doll-like fashion, wanting to be reminded of the freedom of youth, which coincided with the bubble economy era.',
        image: '',
