        embed: '',
        audio: '',
        bgColor: '',
        textColor: '#fff',
        htmlContent:
          '<h5>Studio Bertjan Pot"s Masks</h5><p>I wanted to find out if by <a href="https://player.vimeo.com/video/164438721?autoplay=1&title=0&byline=0&portrait=0">stitching</a> a rope together I could make a large flat carpet. Instead of flat, the samples got curvy. When I was about to give up on the carpet, Vladi came up with the idea of ​​shaping the rope into masks. <a href="sample-story-1">The possibilities are endless</a>, I’m meeting new faces every day.</p><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1494548162494-384bba4ab999?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&ixid=eyJhcHBfaWQiOjEyMDd9&w=1000&q=80" alt="test"><p>This time last year, millions of people descended upon New York City for WorldPride. The event is typically held every couple of years in a different city around the globe, and in 2019 the location was selected to commemorate the 50th anniversary of the Stonewall riots, the uprising led by black and brown queer folks to combat police harassment in the LGBTQ+ community.</p><p>Stonewall riots, the uprising led by black and brown queer folks to combat police harassment in the LGBTQ+ community.</p><ul><li>Lesbian is a homosexual woman</li><li>Gay is a term that primarily refers to a homosexual person or the trait of being homosexual.</li><li>Bisexual is romantic attraction, sexual attraction, or sexual behavior toward both males and females,or to more than one sex or gender.</li><li>Transgender people have a gender identity or gender expression that differs from their sex assigned at birth.</li><li>Queer is an umbrella term for sexual and gender minorities who are not heterosexual and cisgender.</li></ul>',
